          "description": "This place is awful. Besides the fact that I was lectured for daring to step inside the lobby 10 minutes prior to opening (the front entrance was unlocked and ajar), the staff at this location provided inaccurate test results over the phone. I went to Medrite on 3/23 after noticing tonsillitis. A throat culture was done. On 3/28 I called the office to receive results over the phone and was told that I was negative for strep and no follow up was needed, verbatim. On 4/3 I called the office back since my symptoms hadn\u2019t improved. This time I was put in a queue to speak with a provider who told me that I had in fact tested positive for strep. So for over a week I unknowingly exposed friends, family, and colleagues to strep due to incompetence from Medrite staff. I would bet this falls somewhere in the realm of malpractice. Terrible experience from start to finish.",
